McCook, Alison (November 19, 2015), <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://retractionwatch.com/2015/11/19/can-journals-get-hijacked-apparently-yes/\">\"Can journals get hijacked? Apparently, yes\"</a>, <i><a href=\"/wiki/Retraction_Watch\" title=\"Retraction Watch\">Retraction Watch</a></i></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Retraction+Watch&amp;rft.atitle=Can+journals+get+hijacked%3F+Apparently%2C+yes&amp;rft.date=2015-11-19&amp;rft.aulast=McCook&amp;rft.aufirst=Alison&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fretractionwatch.com%2F2015%2F11%2F19%2Fcan-journals-get-hijacked-apparently-yes%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHijacked+journal\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span>.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite id=\"CITEREFBohannon2015\" class=\"citation\">Bohannon, John (November 19, 2015), <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://news.sciencemag.org/scientific-community/2015/11/feature-how-hijack-journal\">\"Feature: How to hijack a journal\"</a>, <i><a href=\"/wiki/Science_(journal)\" title=\"Science (journal)\">Science</a></i>, <a href=\"/wiki/Digital_object_identifier\" title=\"Digital object identifier\">doi</a>:<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//doi.org/10.1126/science.aad7463\">10.1126/science.aad7463</a></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Science&amp;rft.atitle=Feature%3A+How+to+hijack+a+journal&amp;rft.date=2015-11-19&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1126%2Fscience.aad7463&amp;rft.aulast=Bohannon&amp;rft.aufirst=John&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fnews.sciencemag.org%2Fscientific-community%2F2015%2F11%2Ffeature-how-hijack-journal&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHijacked+jour